column5: Definition
column7: Notes [Here you can make notes while you tag images, of what may be outliers, nuances, iffy cases, etc.]

column5: A photo where there is no identifiable subject
A photo where two adults are present
column7: Sometimes age is not clearly identifiable.

column5: A photo where one adult and one child is present
A photo where three adults are present
A photo where one adult and two children are present
A photo where four adults are present
The background is not predominantly black and solid
Patterns or shapes are present in the background of the photo
Text is present in the background of the photo
column7: This includes signs that look like letters but might not be an actual text/language.

column5: A curtain is present in the background of the photo
column7: Curtains were very subtle sometimes, also includes wavy-like structures in the background that are similar to a curtain.

column5: A space where one can go into to have their photograph taken
column7: Sometimes the subject might be sitting in somewhat of a "booth" space, but it was not always clearly a photo booth. Only includes images in which this was clear.

column5: There is another image visible in the background
A photo with the exactness of a photograph
column7: This one can be difficult as sometimes some part of the image looked photorealistic but others did not. Only includes images in which this was clear.

column5: A photo made using animation techniques
The subject looks like their appearance was improved
column7: This one is barely used, because usually it falls more under make-up.

column5: A reflection of the subject is visible
column7: Includes both a reflection by another mirror-like object or a stand-alone mirrored representation of the same subject.

column5: The color of the photo appears more vibrant and intense
The color of the photo appears less vibrant and intense
The color predominantly appears with shades that range from red, orange and yellow to a warm white
The color predominantly appears with more “blue light”
A light that falls on a subject at roughly ninety degrees to the camera
column7: It almost always looked like some shadow was falling onto one side of the face, hinting to side lighting. Used in more obvious cases.

column5: A lamp projecting a beam of light directly on to a subject from above
column7: This is only used if the light was clearly coming from the top, not frontal.

column5: A light that is coming from below the subject
A light that is illuminating the subject from the back
A light that is bright, glowing, and vibrant in appearance, often in electric hues like red, blue, green
A photo in black, white, shades of grey, and no other color
A photo of soft, muted, nostalgic, hazy atmosphere
A photo that results in a darker picture, due to a lack of light
A photo that results in a brighter picture, due to an abundance of light
A photo where the camera axis is slightly tilted away from the vertical
column7: Does not count if the subject themselves is tilting their head or body, it should be the axis of the camera.

column5: A photo that looks like it was taken by the subject themselves
column7: If someone is close-up because it is taken as a selfie, it is labeled only as selfie.

column5: A photo of the subject at close range
column7: Does not include selfies. The face should be clearly enlarged, should not include torso, can include neck.

column5: The subject is fully visible and seems further away
column7: The subject appears small and further away from the camera. Full-body ≠ zoomed-out.

column5: A part of the subject's body is cropped out of the frame
column7: Only count it as "body cut off" if the body is cropped out vertically in the image. If the body is missing because of the original framing — for example, taken in a photobooth that doesn’t show the full body, or a selfie where part of the body is out of frame due to the camera angle — it does not count as cropped off.

column5: The face is partially or completely missing from the image, by being cropped out of the frame
column7: Only includes the face being cut off, starting either vertically or horizontally from the eyebrows (top) or lips (bottom), does not include solely part of e.g. forehead or chin. Thus does not include overall 'head' without part of the face being cut off

column5: A photo that depicts the subject's face partially or fully from the side
column7: Counts as side profile if the contours of the nose are shown clearly by being positioned (slightly) sideways

column5: A photo that is focusing on the face and expression of the subject
column7: Includes full head and torso, including chest, not including waist. Subject should be facing the camera.

column5: Skin that is pulled, twisted out of its original shape
column7: Should include the full-body, although parts of the feet can be slightly cropped off, as long as the body is roughly 95% in frame.

column5: The subject is morphing into another object
column7: The subject is either morphed as stuck in an object, or their body parts fade into the object by color / shape.

column5: A body position in which the knees are to the chest, and arms are wrapped around the knees
A body that appears to be moving while the photo is taken
column7: Images with arms raised often appear to be in motion.

column5: An unconscious body posture, typically with the arms and legs uncrossed
A body posture in which the subject makes themselves smaller
column7: Difficult to code alongside hunched (as in difficult to decide which of the two applied, or both)

column5: A photo in which the legs are uncrossed and open, where the centre of the image is the crotch
A body posture with the legs closed and crossed over one another
column7: Includes both 'kleermakerszit' and crossing one leg over the other

column5: A confident body posture with a straight back and shoulders back
A posture in which the subject is sitting in a drooping way
column7: Usually laid back into the chair/object they appear to be sitting on

column5: Putting the body in a lower, more guarded position
A body where the neck is leaning to one side
Open body language that appears to invite sexual activity
column7: Mostly images taken from above with subject looking up, and arms/hands close to the face or supporting the face (holding it up)

column5: A photo where two or more people are physically touching each other
A body posture in which the shoulders are raised and the torso is bent forward
Attire which is transparent and/or sheer
Attire that is related to a specific cultural background, or which holds specific cultural significance
column7: Includes mostly hijabs.

column5: Attire on which there is a repeated decorative design
Attire for an official, important occasion
Bold, coloured paint to decorate the face
Lacking foot attire, no socks and shoes
column7: Barefoot images often with the feet being showcased, usually an emphasized feature of the image

column5: Attire which is revealing of the skin
Attire which is not the 'norm', and is alternative instead
Distinctive clothing worn by members of the same organization, profession, or school children
column7: Includes waiters and doctors.

column5: Attire that has an image or custom design printed on it
A combination of masculine and feminine characteristics in clothing - unisex
Paint for finger- and toe-nails
column7: Only tagged when obvious, as many of the hands are distorted.

column5: Attire to wrap around one's neck, for warmth and style
Personal ornaments often made of metal that accessorize an outfit
column7: Includes necklaces, bracelets, earrings, rings. Does not include piercings.

column5: A form of body modification where tattoo ink (or dye/pigment) is punctured into the skin to make a (decorative) design
Cosmetics which are applied to the face to enhance or alter the appearance
Decorative objects which can be worn on the head or in the hair
column7: Includes mostly hats and caps, sometimes headbands

column5: Attire to keep the hands covered and warm
column7: Does not include boxing gloves

column5: A pair of lenses set in a frame resting on the nose and ears
Tinted glasses to protect the eyes from sunlight or glare
Jean trousers which have tears in them
Hair grown on the body, usually on the arms and legs
Hair grown on the face, usually on the chin, cheeks, and upper lip area
column7: Mostly men, mostly beards.

column5: A broad and eclectic category of haircuts and styles that break away from mainstream trends
column7: Includes bangs, especially sharp bangs like the example given.

column5: A complex structure or pattern woven into the hair
A hairstyle made of rope-like strands of hair
Hair which has been dyed an unnatural colour
column7: Includes platinum blonde, pink, green, blue, and purple. Not balayage.

column5: A hair type characterized by a springy, corkscrew-type texture
The fingers are curled inward and the thumb rests against or around them, forming a closed shape
A specific positioning of the fingers/hand used to convey a symbol, gesture, or meaning
column7: The depicted symbol include a specific concept or idea, such as victory, peace, 'rock out', or similar.

column5: Extending one finger in a specific direction to point at a particular object or thing
column7: Clear to convey a specific action or indication.

column5: A gesture/greeting with one hand raised and fingers spread open, with the palm facing outward
column7: Often includes eye contact from the subject, perhaps resembling a direct greeting to the camera, typical of real photographs.

column5: Two hands from the same subject touching or intertwined
column7: It includes highly deformed hands but whose arms converge in the same direction recalling the gesture.

column5: One or both hands positioned near to/touching the face
column7: The hands should visibly interact with the face, either through a touch of fingers or the full contact of the entire hand.

column5: A posture where both hands are placed on top of the head/hair
column7: The hands are visibly positioned on the head.

column5: The hands are bound together with a restraint around the wrists
column7: Where present, the object to be handcuffed must be clear and visible.

column5: A gesture where two people grasp each other's hands, intertwining them
The hands appear misshapen, disproportionate, or anatomically incorrect
column7: Contains minor distortions; during annotation, zooming was often utilized to detect and analyze imperfection.

column5: An object for reaching high surfaces
The visible, glowing part of a fire
A rectangular object that can contain other items
column7: Can relate to a small box, or even a large box that the subject is sitting in, which is clearly not a booth or chair.

column5: A symbol that represents an existing company
column7: Only should be tagged if the brand is existent.

column5: An object that can be worn to carry other small items
column7: Includes handbag, backpack, clutch, purse, shopper, etc.

column5: A container with handles or grips that is used for traveling
column7: Also includes e.g. a suitcase for work purposes.

column5: A round orange object that is used in sport
column7: Could also include (sports) ball in the broadest sense.

column5: A two wheeled vehicle used for transport
column7: Includes also (non-electric) (kids) scooter or step.

column5: A short narrow board with four wheels, on which a subject can ride
column7: Also includes pennyboard or snowboard.

column5: A circular object, that can rotate around the body
column7: Should be annotated as hula hoop if there is clearly a circular shaped tube present in the image, even it's not fully visible.

column5: Protective gloves used during boxing training and fights
column7: Does not include other sorts of gloves.

column5: A set of printed that contain information
column7: If the book does not have a hard cover it is still considered a book, even if its a stack of printed pages.

column5: An object for producing musical sounds
column7: Includes e.g., (electric) guitar, piano, cello, keyboard, etc.

column5: A thing that represents or stands for something else
column7: Covers the representation of latent symbolism, e.g. a heart, but not a symbol as in hand signs.

column5: A plaque that conveys information, meaning, or direction
column7: Should be tagged if the sign does not contain text but is still a sheet or plaque held up by the subject in the image.

column5: A blade fixed into a handle, used for cutting
column7: Can be any sort of knife regardless of its size. Would also include other blade-like objects, such as a sword.

column5: A deep, round container with handles used for cooking
column7: Can be either worn by the subject in the image (e.g. on their head), or placed on top of a surface.

column5: A liquid substance consumed for hydration, nourishment, or enjoyment
column7: Pertains to the container that a drink is held in, does not clearly have to contain the drink to be annotated as 'drink'.

column5: A substance consumed for nourishment
A photograph of a subject other than the one originally pictured
column7: Should either be a printed or digital image of another subject which is clearly not present in the photo booth with the main subject.

column5: An electronic device equipped with a keyboard, either a desktop or laptop
A device for recording and amplifying sound
column7: Can be either a stand-alone microphone or attached to a headset.

column5: An object capable of photographing
column7: Only includes non-phones, if a picture is taken with a phone it should be labeled as phone, not camera. So digital or professional photo cameras only.

column5: A wearable audio and recording device
column7: Includes headphones and (wireless) earbuds.

column5: An electronic device with which to contact others
column7: Includes both modern (smart) and retro representations of a phone.

column5: A portable electronic device, combines functions of a computer and a smartphone
column7: Phone but represented larger, should not contain a keyboard but a clear screen at least.

column5: A woven structure made of interconnected threads
column7: If this pattern is e.g. woven into a chair, it should still be separately tagged as net.

column5: A flat, horizontal surface supported by legs
column7: Legs can be cut out of the image to be annotated as table, if there's a flat surface with items placed on top, we assume it's a table.

column5: Yellowish dried grass, often comes in barrels
A thin, cylindrical roll of finely cut tobacco for smoking
A piece of text written on paper, potentially enclosed in an envelope
column7: Also includes solely the envelope without the presence of the letter.

column5: An object or symbol that holds specific religious significance
column7: Does not include religious or cultural attire, only separate symbolism.

column5: An official document for identification
A long, sturdy seat
column7: Should not have a backrest.

column5: A piece of furniture used for sleeping or resting
column7: Should clearly have e.g. sheets, case or pillow.

column5: A piece of furniture for sitting
column7: Takes chair in the broadest sense, includes couch, sofa, chair, stool, pouf, lounge chair, rocking chair. Does not include bench or bed.

column5: An image or a structural border within another
column7: Can be a picture or mirror frame, or just an item which is frame-shaped.

column5: A red fluid that circulates within the human body
An object which is unclear to the naked eye
column7: Includes any object which is clearly present in the images but too ambigiuous to assume.

column5: A living organism belonging to the animal kingdom
column7: Includes an inanimate animal (e.g. plushie, toy)

column5: A protective device worn on the head
column7: Includes sports and astronaut helmet.

column5: A firearm
An accessory for the wrist to tell the time
column7: If based on color and thickness of the band it is similar to a watch, it is safe to tag it as watch, even if the clock is not as evident.

column5: Does not include eyes. Although the face is clearly deformed, it is possible to argue that the subject represents human features. It includes significant deformations, yet the face still retains anthropomorphic characteristics
The state of being heavier-set, above average weight
The state of being thinner-set, below average weight
Having well-developed, well-defined muscles
Loose skin that has little to no definition
A mark on the body showing the natural healing and replacing of lost skin
Skin that is pulled, twisted out of its original shape
column7: Includes only deformed skin.

column5: A body that is pulled, twisted out of its original shape
column7: Deformation of body parts only is noted.

column5: The eyes are directed downward, not making eye contact with the camera
The eyes are turned to the side, and the gaze directed clearly away from the camera
The eyes are directed upward, with the gaze clearly focused above the horizontal line of sight
column7: Subject must clearly look above themselves.

column5: The eyes are pointed directly at the camera, with the gaze clearly focused on the viewer
column7: The recreated images resemble a photobooth, where, whenever possible, the AI replicates the appearance of a subject as if photographed inside such devices

column5: One or both eyes appear abnormal or altered in shape, size, or position, such as being stretched, widened, or exaggerated
column7: Include minor distortions, as they may appear significant when examined under zoom

column5: The eyelids are fully shut, covering the eyes with no visible openings
The face is so distorted or abstracted that it no longer resembles a recognizable human face
column7: Includes highly deformed faces, the malformations are so prevalent that nothing of the face is recognizable.

column5: The face where features such as the nose, mouth, and cheeks are altered, stretched or exaggerated in shape or proportion
column7: Does not include eyes. Although the face is clearly deformed, it is possible to argue that the character represents human features. It includes significant deformations, yet the face still retains anthropomorphic characteristics

column5: The hands are placed in front of face, either partially or fully hiding it
column7: The face or the mouth should be barely noticeable.

column5: The mouth is obscured or restrained by an object, such as tape, cloth, or another material, preventing it from being visible
A facial expression where the mouth is open, showing visible teeth as part of the smile
A facial expression where the mouth is curved upward in a smile, but the teeth are not visible
The forehead that appears larger than typical, often in proportion to the rest of the face
column7: Includes enlargement that is pronounced and clearly visible.

column5: A facial expression where the lips are pursed and pushed outward
The subject depicted in the photo seems to express positive emotions
The subject depicted in the photo seems to express negative emotions
